1.1 What is Power BI?
Power BI is Microsoft's business intelligence tool that lets you connect to data, transform it, build a data model, and create interactive reports and dashboards — all in one place.

It has three main components:

Power BI Desktop — the free authoring tool you install on your computer. This is where you build everything.
Power BI Service — the online platform (app.powerbi.com) where you publish and share reports with your team.
Power BI Mobile — a mobile app to view reports on the go.
💡 As a report builder, you will spend 95% of your time in Power BI Desktop.

1.2 Requesting Power BI Installation
Submit an IT request through your organization's helpdesk portal
Request: "Power BI Desktop — latest version"
Specify: No admin rights needed — it can be installed from the Microsoft Store
License needed: Power BI Pro (required for sharing reports with others)
Free license = you can build but not share
Pro license = build + share + collaborate
Contact your manager to approve the Pro license if not already assigned
1.3 Installing Power BI Desktop
Option A — Microsoft Store (recommended, no IT needed):

Open the Microsoft Store on your computer
Search for "Power BI Desktop"
Click Install
Launch from Start Menu when done
Option B — Direct download:

Go to: https://powerbi.microsoft.com/downloads
Click Download Free
Run the installer (.exe file)
Follow the setup wizard
1.4 First-Time Setup
Launch Power BI Desktop
Sign in with your organizational email (not personal Gmail)
Go to File → Options and Settings → Options
Under Regional Settings → set locale to match your data format
Under Python Scripting → set your Python path if using Python visuals
