5.1 Filter Context vs Row Context (Plain English)
Filter Context — the set of filters currently active when a measure is evaluated. Think of it as "what the user has selected on the report" (slicers, visual filters, page filters).

Row Context — exists when DAX is iterating row by row through a table. This happens inside calculated columns and iterator functions like SUMX, MAXX.

💡 CALCULATE is the most important DAX function — it changes the filter context before evaluating an expression.

5.2 Core Functions Reference
Aggregation:

[Total Allowance] = SUM('Fact'[TOTAL_ALLOWANCE])
[Avg EL]          = AVERAGE('Fact'[EL])
[Unique Quarters] = DISTINCTCOUNT('Fact'[PER_QTR])
Logic:

[Label] = IF([Total EL] > 0, "Positive", "Zero or Negative")
[Label] = SWITCH(SELECTEDVALUE('Table'[Step]), "A", 1, "B", 2, BLANK())
[Value] = COALESCE([Measure1], [Measure2], 0)
Filter:

[Base EL] = CALCULATE(SUM('Fact'[EL]), 'Fact'[SCENARIO] = "BASE")
[All EL]  = CALCULATE(SUM('Fact'[EL]), ALL('Fact'))
Iterator:

[Weighted EL] = SUMX('Fact', 'Fact'[EL] * 'Fact'[WEIGHT])
[Peak Quarter] = MAXX(TOPN(1, SUMMARIZE(...), [Value], DESC), 'Fact'[PER_QTR])
5.3 Always Use VAR / RETURN
VAR stores a result so it can be reused. It also makes debugging much easier.

[My Measure] =
VAR _base   = CALCULATE(SUM('Fact'[EL]), 'Fact'[SCENARIO] = "BASE")
VAR _stress = CALCULATE(SUM('Fact'[EL]), 'Fact'[SCENARIO] = "STRESS")
VAR _diff   = _base - _stress
RETURN
    DIVIDE(_diff, _base, 0)
💡 To debug: temporarily change RETURN to return any intermediate VAR (e.g. RETURN _base) to inspect its value.

5.4 Common Measure Patterns
Rolling 9-Quarter Window:

[Cum 9Q EL PQ0] =
CALCULATE(
    SUM('Fact'[TOTAL_ALLOWANCE]),
    'Fact'[SCENARIO]  = "BASE",
    'Fact'[I_SEGMENT] = "SVB",
    'Fact'[PER_QTR]  >= 0,
    'Fact'[PER_QTR]  <= 8
)
OR Filter for data gaps:

[EL SVB BASE] =
VAR _svb =
    CALCULATE(SUM('Fact'[EL]),
        'Fact'[SCENARIO]  = "BASE",
        'Fact'[I_SEGMENT] = "SVB")
VAR _gb =
    CALCULATE(SUM('Fact'[EL]),
        'Fact'[SCENARIO]  = "BASE",
        'Fact'[I_SEGMENT] = "General Bank",
        'Fact'[PORTFOLIO] = "SVB")
RETURN
    COALESCE(_svb, 0) + COALESCE(_gb, 0)
Waterfall Offset:

[Waterfall Amount] =
VAR EndACL   = [Ending ACL RUFC]
VAR Prov2Top = [Peak ACL] + [Provision 2]
RETURN
    SWITCH(SELECTEDVALUE('Steps'[StepKey]),
        "NCO2", Prov2Top - EndACL,
        ...
    )
