6.1 What is DAX Studio?
DAX Studio is a free external tool that connects to your Power BI Desktop file and lets you write, test, and debug DAX queries directly — without affecting your report.

Download: https://daxstudio.org

6.2 Connecting to Power BI Desktop
Open your .pbix file in Power BI Desktop
Open DAX Studio
Select "PBI / SSDT Model" from the connection dialog
Choose your open Power BI file from the list
Click Connect
6.3 Running a Query
Every DAX Studio query starts with EVALUATE:

-- View a full table
EVALUATE 'FactAllowance'

-- Filter a table
EVALUATE
FILTER(
    'FactAllowance',
    'FactAllowance'[SCENARIO] = "BASE"
)

-- Test a measure
EVALUATE
ROW("Result", [Total Allowance BASE SVB])
6.4 Debugging a Measure with DEFINE
DEFINE
    MEASURE 'Fact'[_Debug] =
        VAR _base = CALCULATE(SUM('Fact'[EL]), 'Fact'[SCENARIO] = "BASE")
        RETURN _base   -- return any VAR to inspect it

EVALUATE
ROW("Debug Value", 'Fact'[_Debug])
💡 This lets you test measures without creating them in Power BI first.

6.5 Performance — Server Timings
Click Server Timings button in the toolbar
Run your query
Look at Total time and Storage Engine vs Formula Engine split
High Formula Engine time → your DAX logic is complex, simplify it
High Storage Engine time → your model may need optimization
