8.1 When to Use Python (The Escalation Rule)
Only use Python when:

A native Power BI visual cannot produce the chart you need
The DAX required would be so complex it hurts performance
⚠️ Python visuals are static — they do not respond to slicers or cross-filtering.

8.2 Setup
Install Python from https://python.org (version 3.9+ recommended)
Install required libraries — open Command Prompt and run:
pip install pandas matplotlib seaborn
In Power BI Desktop → File → Options → Python Scripting
Set the Python home directory to your installation path
8.3 Example — Heatmap
python
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# 'dataset' is the Power BI dataframe passed automatically
pivot = dataset.pivot(index="I_SEGMENT", columns="PER_QTR", values="EL")

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
sns.heatmap(pivot, annot=True, fmt=".1f", cmap="RdYlGn")
plt.title("EL Heatmap by Segment and Quarter")
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
