DAX Issues
Measure returns BLANK unexpectedly → Wrap with COALESCE([Measure], 0) or check if filter context is too restrictive

CALCULATE not applying filter → Make sure you are using column filters (Table[Col] = "Value") not measure filters

Circular dependency error → You are referencing a measure inside a calculated column in the same table — move logic to a measure instead

Power Query Issues
"We cannot convert value to type Text" → Use Text.From([Column]) inline instead of Table.TransformColumnTypes

Column not found after source change → Go to Applied Steps → find the step that references the missing column → update the column name

Slow refresh times → Filter rows early in the query (Step 1 or 2) to reduce volume before transformations

Visual Issues
Waterfall bars misaligned → Check that Waterfall Start + Waterfall Amount = Waterfall End for every step

Slicer not filtering all pages → Go to View → Sync Slicers → enable sync for all pages

Python visual not rendering → Check Python path in Options → ensure pandas and matplotlib are installed

FAQs
Q: What is the difference between a measure and a calculated column? A: A measure is calculated on demand when a visual renders. A calculated column is calculated at refresh and stored in the model. Use measures for aggregations, calculated columns for row-level labels.

Q: Why is my report slow? A: Most likely causes — too many calculated columns, bidirectional relationships, or complex DAX with nested FILTER(ALL(...)) patterns.

Q: Can two people edit the same .pbix file at the same time? A: No. Power BI Desktop does not support co-authoring. Use Power BI Service workspaces for collaboration.

